@startuml 21_CRAG_Retrieval_Strategy
!theme plain
title 3D Data Quality Framework -- CRAG / CAG Retrieval Strategy

skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam defaultFontName Segoe UI
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #546E7A
  LifeLineBorderColor #B0BEC5
  ParticipantBorderColor #90A4AE
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #ECEFF1
  BoxBorderColor #CFD8DC
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #FFFDE7
  BorderColor #F9A825
}

participant "DQ Backend\nApp" as Backend
participant "CAG\nPre-Loader\n(static docs)" as CAG #DCEDC8
participant "Vector Search\nIndex\n(BGE-M3)" as VectorIdx #C5CAE9
participant "CRAG\nRetrieval\nEvaluator" as CRAG #FFCDD2
participant "Query\nRewriter" as Rewriter #FFF9C4
participant "LLM\nSQL Generator" as LLM #E8F5E9
participant "Documentation\nStore\n(UC Volume)" as Docs

== Step A: CAG -- Static Context Pre-Load (always runs first) ==

note over CAG
  Context-Augmented Generation (CAG):
  Pre-loads small, stable documents ONCE per session
  into the fixed portion of every LLM prompt.
  No retrieval cost. No chunking errors.
  Documents:
    supported_checks.md  (all valid check types + rules)
    security_patterns.json  (blocked SQL patterns)
  Together ~3,200 tokens -- always in system prompt.
end note

Backend -> CAG : get_static_context()
activate CAG
CAG --> Backend : {supported_checks_text, security_patterns_text}
deactivate CAG

note right of Backend
  CAG context injected as [SYSTEM] block
  in every LLM call. Ensures the model
  ALWAYS knows the check catalogue and
  security rules -- no retrieval gap.
end note

== Step B: CRAG -- Dynamic Context Retrieval with Confidence Gate ==

Backend -> VectorIdx : embed_and_search(\n  query="{check_type} {table} {column} {domain}",\n  top_k=8,\n  filter={doc_type, table_name})
activate VectorIdx
VectorIdx -> Docs : cosine similarity lookup\nagainst BGE-M3 chunk index
Docs --> VectorIdx : ranked chunks[]
VectorIdx --> Backend : top_k chunks + similarity_scores[]
deactivate VectorIdx

Backend -> CRAG : evaluate_retrieval(\n  query, top_k_chunks, scores[])
activate CRAG

note right of CRAG
  CRAG Retrieval Evaluator:
  Scores overall relevance of the retrieved
  chunk set against the user query.
  Algorithm:
    1. Per-chunk relevance score (cosine sim)
    2. Coverage score: key entities from
       query covered in returned chunks?
    3. Composite confidence = weighted avg
       of top-3 chunk scores * coverage
  Thresholds (configurable):
    confidence >= 0.72  -> HIGH   -> use as-is
    0.50 <= conf < 0.72 -> MEDIUM -> rewrite + retry
    confidence < 0.50   -> LOW    -> fallback path
end note

CRAG --> Backend : {confidence: HIGH | MEDIUM | LOW,\n score: float,\n missing_entities: []}
deactivate CRAG

== CRAG Branch: HIGH confidence (>= 0.72) ==

alt confidence == HIGH
  note right of Backend
    Retrieved chunks are relevant.
    Proceed directly to SQL generation
    with standard RAG context window.
  end note
  Backend -> LLM : generate_sql(\n  cag_context + rag_context)
  activate LLM
  LLM --> Backend : {sql, explanation}
  deactivate LLM

== CRAG Branch: MEDIUM confidence (0.50 - 0.72) -- Rewrite + Retry ==

else confidence == MEDIUM
  note right of Backend
    Confidence uncertain. Retrieval may
    have missed relevant context.
    Trigger query rewrite and one retry.
  end note

  Backend -> Rewriter : rewrite_query(\n  original_query,\n  missing_entities[],\n  check_type)
  activate Rewriter
  note right of Rewriter
    Query Rewriter expands the query:
    - Adds synonyms for missing entities
    - Includes table alias from UC metadata
    - Adds domain glossary term expansions
    e.g. "null check customer email"
      -> "NULL_RATE null_check customer_email
          gold.customer CRM PII nullable"
  end note
  Rewriter --> Backend : rewritten_query
  deactivate Rewriter

  Backend -> VectorIdx : embed_and_search(\n  rewritten_query, top_k=12)
  activate VectorIdx
  VectorIdx --> Backend : expanded top_k chunks
  deactivate VectorIdx

  Backend -> CRAG : re_evaluate(rewritten_query, chunks)
  activate CRAG
  CRAG --> Backend : {confidence: HIGH | LOW, score}
  deactivate CRAG

  alt re-eval confidence >= 0.50
    Backend -> LLM : generate_sql(cag_context + expanded_rag_context)
    activate LLM
    LLM --> Backend : {sql, explanation,\n warning: "low_confidence_retrieval"}
    deactivate LLM
    note right of LLM
      SQL generated but flagged with
      confidence warning surfaced to user:
      "Retrieved context was partial --
       please review the generated SQL carefully."
    end note
  else re-eval still LOW
    Backend --> Backend : escalate to LOW path
  end

== CRAG Branch: LOW confidence (< 0.50) -- Fallback ==

else confidence == LOW
  note right of Backend
    Retrieved chunks are not relevant.
    Two fallback options executed in order:
    1. Keyword search (no embeddings) against
       the same UC Volume corpus.
    2. If still no match: ask user for DDL /
       data contract before attempting SQL gen.
  end note

  Backend -> Docs : keyword_search(\n  terms=missing_entities[],\n  doc_types=[data_contract, sql_pattern])
  activate Docs
  Docs --> Backend : keyword_matched_chunks[]
  deactivate Docs

  alt keyword_matched_chunks not empty
    Backend -> LLM : generate_sql(\n  cag_context + keyword_context,\n  low_confidence=true)
    activate LLM
    LLM --> Backend : {sql, explanation,\n warning: "fallback_keyword_context"}
    deactivate LLM
  else no context found at all
    Backend --> Backend : return no_context_error
    note right of Backend
      Return structured error to Genie:
      {error: "insufficient_context",
       missing: [table_schema, check_definition],
       ask_user: "Please paste the table DDL
                  or data contract for this table."}
    end note
  end

end

== Step C: Confidence Signal Written to check_suggestions_cache ==

note over Backend
  Regardless of CRAG path taken, the confidence score
  and retrieval quality signal are written to
  check_suggestions_cache alongside the generated suggestion.
  This feeds the CRAG evaluator's calibration:
    table_fqn + schema_version -> confidence_score, path_taken,
    chunks_used[], query_rewritten (bool), sql_accepted (bool)
  After 30 accepted suggestions, evaluator thresholds
  are auto-tuned per domain using the feedback signal.
end note

legend
  <b>How to read this diagram</b>
  -------------------------------------------------------
  <b>WHAT:</b> Reliability layer on top of RAG for the DQ
  rule authoring copilot. Prevents LLM from generating
  SQL with wrong columns or unknown check types due to
  low-quality retrieved context (hallucination risk).

  <b>WHY TWO STRATEGIES?</b>
  CAG: small, stable docs injected once per session.
    No retrieval cost. No chunking errors. Always correct.
  CRAG: dynamic docs scored before LLM sees them.
    Catches bad retrieval before it causes bad SQL.

  <b>HOW CRAG DECIDES</b>
  HIGH (>=0.72): retrieved chunks are relevant -> proceed.
  MEDIUM (0.50-0.72): expand query + retry with top-12.
  LOW (<0.50): keyword fallback. Ask user for DDL if empty.

  <b>WHAT IS ACHIEVED</b>
  Eliminates check-type hallucinations (CAG catalogue).
  Catches retrieval misses before SQL is generated.
  Confidence signal enables per-domain threshold tuning.

  <b>HOW IT IS MEASURED</b>
  Avg CRAG confidence score per domain (target >0.72).
  Query rewrite trigger rate (MEDIUM branch frequency).
  LLM SQL acceptance rate stored in check_suggestions_cache.
endlegend

@enduml
